content.problem:
If $\displaystyle g(x) = \int_0^x f(t)\dt$ and the graph of $f$ 
is given below, sketch the graph of $g$. At what value of $x$ does 
$g$ have a maximum?

\begin{center}
\begin{tikzpicture}
 \begin{axis}[
 width=8cm, height=4cm,
 axis lines=middle,
 xlabel={$t$}, ylabel={$f(t)$},
 xmin=-0.5, xmax=6.5,
 ymin=-2, ymax=3,
 xtick={0,1,...,6},
 ytick={-1,1,2},
 every axis x label/.style={at={(ticklabel* cs:1)}, anchor=west},
 ]
 \addplot[AtlasTeal, thick] coordinates 
 {(0,0) (1,2) (2,2) (3,0) (4,-1) (5,-1) (6,0)};
 \end{axis}
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{center}
